addFields

public void addFields(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                      int method,
                      java.lang.String... properties)
Adds fields of correct type for all specified properties of the specified class. Supports all Field-Types of the package panama.form. For other property-values a basic Field is created. If properties are not found or some reflections goes wrong, errors are logged at debug-level. If unknown properties are specified, _no_ fields are added.

Parameters:
clazz - A class
method - what to do with properties: INCLUDE_PROPERTIES: add fields for specified properties, EXCLUDE_PROPERTIES: add fields for all _but_ the specified properties.
properties - names of properties to be included or excluded
